The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 08 November is 6,736 (779.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 November, there were 849 new confirmed cases (98.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 27 October, there were 806 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% ( 43 extra cases).
